Well I'm sitting here. Bored. Waiting. Again. School kinda sucks but whatever. I'm hungry...I want chicken pad thai! Nothing particulary interesting happened today, except my car really broke down today and I left it at the garage and was supposed to pick it up at 5pm and I forgot and didn't get there til' 5:11pm and he was already gone. So...no car. And I gotta work tomorrow at 10am so...not sure how thats gonna happen since he doesn't usually open til 10 anyways. Oh well. If Alex had been here when he said he would...it would have been fine. I just wish he would get here...I'm hungry. LOL Last night weren't too good either. My womens studies class ran late and didn't get outta there til' almost 10pm at which point it was pouring rain and my car wasn't running right so I went home instead of going over to Crystals like I was supposed to. So Amie and Crystal are probably mad. Ehhh....oh well. Everyone eventually gets mad at me lol. Well, I'm gonna go even though I have no where to go TO, oh well. :)  I love saying oh well. I sound so care-free.

Sarah

Hello everybody. Its been a long time since I've updated my journal, but don't worry not too much has been happening! First off schools okay I suppose. My friends for the most part seem to be doing well. Except for poor Amie whose been having a hard time lately, and I hope feels better REAL SOON! I love you Amie!

       The family is pretty good, Dad doesn't seem as sick lately and has stopped the treatments that were making him so sick. Mumsy's good. Abby has like pneomonia (s.p?) or something and shes been real sick but she'll be alright. Toby and Tilly are same as ever. My grammy seems better also, not as depressed since my grandfather passed away.

        Now brings me to the somewhat exciting part....Alex! heheheh I love him so much! Anyways, I might be getting an engagement ring for Christmas! YAY for me! It's not definate, but very probable. We wouldn't be getting married for quite a while, at least a couple years, but I'm soo excited. Hes also told me we should start saving for an apartment :)  yay!  God, I sound soooooo juvenile...oh well.

        As for just me, I've been okay. I always get a little depressed at the end of fall when winter is fast approaching. I think or the grey skies and cold slush that seeps into boots, and the gusting icy winds that burn your skin. LOL anyways, I'll be fine.

          Well, I g2g leave me some comments, that is if anyones actually reading this thing. If not I guess this journal's more private than I thought. :)

                          Love to All,

                              Sarah

Some people just plain SUCK! These are, among others, people who are sneaky liars, who you can never trust. The particular jerk I am thinking of today, happens to be one whom I signed up for classes with because at the time he was a nice guy. Both of the classes he suggested. The first class was kayaking. I signed up for it thinking okay well it'll be cool I'll have someone I know with me..sure why not. Well I'll tell you why not. It started off we were late driving up there, so he drove 120 mph! I know a lot of people are like "wow, thats cool!" Well, I'm not, I happen to have known people who died in car accidents. And swerving around at 120 mph put my life, his life, and everyone on the roads life in danger. I let that go because we were, afterall, late for class. Then we got to this wonderful class and I had to put a wetsuit on that didn't fit by any stretch of the imagination...and I was extremely uncomfortable all day. Then I got seasick. Wow, that was fun. But neither the suit or the sickness was his fault. However, when lunch rolled around all I wanted to do was sit in the car (that makes me feel better usually) and eat my lunch. But this particular guy refused to let me sit in his car because "I don't want saltwater on the seats", this is strange when you consider that not even my feet had been in the water. I told him that I was completely dry with no saltwater anywheres and he said "I don't care I don't want you in my car" What an ASS! If I was in his postion, even if the person was soaking wet, I would let a sick person sit down in my car! It's funny how he has such a lack of empathy, when you consider his current profession! Anyways then we have to get back in the boats, and we're supposed to practice rescues. Since I was feeling really sick, I asked if he wanted to get in the water and I'd rescue him. He said No, which would have been fine. Except that after a while he decided he would go in, and he told me that. So I helped him while he took off his sneakers, which he put in my boat. Finally, when he was all ready (in front of a group of people) he was like "Alright, now I gotta find someone to rescue me" and I was like "Gee, thanks ___" Oh well, he only picked some skinny blond girl (who he ended up flipping over anyways) :) and who had already had a chance to rescue a bunch of people. but whatever, I wouldn't wanna rescue him anyways.  Finally the day was over, and we got in the car and headed for home. Well down the long winding, narrow road from the beach he averaged 70-80 mph. Very dangerous. Meanwhile I told him I had to go the bathroom and asked if I should wait til Brunswick, he said yeah wait. Well I didn't get to use the bathroom till Portland. But that wasn't that long of a drive since he went 110 mph the whole way back, through afternoon traffic. He swerved and dodged cars and braked at the last minute. I was desperate to get out of the car. It was awful. It was a terrible day. That'll def. teach me not to take classes with people I know. Because what could seem like a really nice guy at the beginning of the summer might turn out to be a prick to you in the fall. On top of all that I also got a very nice bladder infection from not being able to go to the bathroom, I wish I had peed on his precious seats!! :)
      I'm not writing this to be mean to any of his friends, or girlfriend. I'm writing this so that if they should happen to read this they can know what a jerk he was to me. And if he can be that rude and mean to me what makes you think he can't be to you?!  Oh yeah I also forgot to tell you that he secretly dropped the other class I had with him, psychology, w/o saying anything to me, the last day of the drop period. So that I would be stuck in it, alone. In a class he picked. Yeah Thanks a Lot! Really nice! If he had been at all decent he would have at least  told me so that I could have thought about whether or not to stay in the class. Too late now! Whatever, I'm def. better off without that in my class.
      What really pisses me off is that I was nice and courteous towards him. I should have told him what an arrogant prick he really is. Thinking hes all great. Not caring at all about others (except a select few) But again too late for that, cause I don't wanna talk to him again-ever. Oh and I pray that he gets pulled over and gets his license taken away, before someone gets killed. He must be pretty stupid to think that its safe for him to be driving that way. I hope I hope someone with a brain can tell him to drive better and not go 60mph over the speed limit. I worry about my friends who drive with him, and urge them not to. I don't wanna go to any funerals!
      Thanks for Reading,
           Sarah

Your Life Path Number Is 7
7
You are a peaceful and affectionate soul... and by nature rather reserved and analytical. The overwhelming strength of the number 7 is reflected in the depth of thinking that is shown. You will garner knowledge from practically every source that you find. Intellectual, scientific and studious, you don't accept a premise until you have dissected the subject and arrived at you own independent conclusion. This is a very spiritual number and it often denotes a sort of spiritual wisdom that becomes apparent at a fairly early age. You need a good deal of quiet time to be with your own inner thoughts and dreams. You dislike crowds, noise and confusion. You are very thorough and complete in your work, the perfectionist who expects everyone else to be a meet a high standard of performance, too. You evaluate situations very quickly and with amazing accuracy. You rely heavily on your experiences and your intuition, rather than accepting advice from someone. Your hunches usually prove to be very accurate, and knowing this, you are one who tends to follow the directions they seem to guide. It's easy for you to detect deception and recognize insincere people. You aren't one to have a wide circle of friends, but once you accept someone as a friend, it's for life. You really aren't a very social person, and your reserve is often taken to be aloofness. You actually like being alone, away from the hustle and bustle of modern life. In many ways, you would have fit in better in much earlier times when the pace of life was less hectic. In the most negative use of the 7 energies, you can become very pessimistic, lackadaisical, quarrelsome, and secretive. A Life Path 7 individual who is not living life fully and gaining through experiences. A negative 7 is a hard person to live with because of a serious lack of consideration. The negative 7 is very selfish and spoiled. If you have any of the negative traits they are very difficult to get rid of. At your worst, you feel that the world really does owe you something - or in some way you aren't being fairly treated. Fortunately, the negative 7 is not the typical 7, at least not without some mitigating positive traits. This number is one that seems to have some major shifts from highs to lows. Stability in feelings may be elusive for you.

I feel like I can never be honest with anyone. I feel as though no one really wants me to be honest. Either they don't care enough to hear my crap. Or they don't want to hear anything that may upset them...even if it means a constant nagging pain to me. I feel trapped and tortured a lot of my time. Trapped inside a jar of lies. Tortured by the pressure to say the right thing, do the right thing, be the right person. I don't wanna be that person anymore. I feel repressed- smothered. I can't take it anymore. Being always the way I'm supposed to be! I have done so many things I didn't want to do. I have lied to every person I know at least 10 times...at least. And its not that I don't love them- it's that I do. If I didn't care I wouldn't take the time to lie. 
     I have loved people who could never know. I think about people who I shoudn't. I want to say something, but I can't. I want to tell them I care but instead I walk away. Because I know that someone will get hurt, me or them...but someone. But I am hurting anyways. But I care...
     Then I see people who don't ever seem to care about anyone else. They laugh and flirt as they please...and enjoy life. And I think why can't I be that way? Why do I always try to deny my feelings whileeveryone else has a good time? 
     Gotta go now LOL.....wow <3~Sarah

Once upon a time there was a girl named Sarah. Sarah lived in a cold Arctic-esque place. She was young and nice and had a few pretty great friends. People liked her pretty well, and she liked them. Uh huh! She did. She had two very good friends named Crytal and Amelia. They were the best of friends. Sarah would dress Amelia up in GoodWill wedding gowns. They would all hang out at Crystals place. It was fairly decent times in the life of Sarah!

     Then one fateful day, Sarahs friend Ray-Ray introduced Crystal to...**gasp** a crazy guy. Before it could be stopped Crystal had been "boy-crazyified"! YIKES! She stopped wanting to hang out and try on mildewy dresses. She stopped having time for anyone other than Him! She no longer returned calls, nor meant to. Amelia and Sarah were at a loss for words...they didn't know what to say. They wanted their friend to be happy...but was she? Could she be happy with her every move being watched? How could our once-free-spirited pal Crystal, be alright with being controlled? What could they do?.....

      Sarah and Amelia decided it was time to take matters into their own hands...so on the day of love....(a.k.a Valentines Day, in case you didn't know) they decided to kidnap her and take her away from the scary monster guy...They had to time everything perfectly because she wouldn't have more than two minutes alone all day...and that would be as she was leaving her job at the artist gallery, where she made statue-type edible displays, using meats and vegetables. Amelia and Sarah got there just in time... They told her that they had something to show her in the trunk, she hesitated...she had to get home to Him! She went around back to look and Sarah and Amelia pushed her into the trunk.

     They drove around for a while not entirely sure where to take her. Finally they decided to drive down to Florida to see their other friend, Nathalia. Nathalia was soooo happy to see them both...they let crystal out of the trunk. She was a little angry that she had been shoved into a trunk and kidnapped, but she quickly got over it when she saw that she was in sunny Florida with her bestest friends and that they could go swimming, instead of skiing! YAY! So everything worked out in the end...and He found somebody else who really liked being controlled...and all was well in the life of Sarah, Amelia, Crystal, and of course Nathalia!

                            THE END
